      • getOrConnect

        public TcpIpConnection getOrConnect(Address address,
                                    boolean silent)
        Description copied from interface: EndpointManager
        Gets the existing connection for a given address. If it does not exist, the system will try to connect asynchronously. In this case, it returns null.

        When the connection is established at some point in time, it can be retrieved using the EndpointManager.getConnection(Address).

        Specified by:
        getOrConnect in interface EndpointManager<TcpIpConnection>
        Parameters:
        address - the address to connect to
        silent - if logging should be done on debug level (silent=true) or on info level (silent=false)
        Returns:
        the existing connection

        public boolean transmit(Packet packet,
                        TcpIpConnection connection)
        Description copied from interface: EndpointManager
        Transmits a packet to a certain connection.

        If this method is called with a null connection, the call returns false.

        Specified by:
        transmit in interface EndpointManager<TcpIpConnection>
        Parameters:
        packet - the packet to transmit
        connection - he connection to where the Packet should be transmitted
        Returns:
        true if the transmit was a success, false if a failure (there is no guarantee that the packet is actually going to be received since the packet perhaps is stuck in some buffer; it just means that it's buffered somewhere)

      • transmit

        public boolean transmit(Packet packet,
                        Address target)
        Description copied from interface: EndpointManager
        Transmits a packet to a certain address.

        If the connection to the target doesn't exist yet, the system will try to make the connection. In this case true can be returned, even though the connection eventually can't be established.

        Specified by:
        transmit in interface EndpointManager<TcpIpConnection>
        Parameters:
        packet - The Packet to transmit.
        target - The address of the target machine where the Packet should be transmitted.
        Returns:
        true if the transmit was a success, false if a failure.
        See Also:
